history.content: The wait list was full but I've just expanded it so you should now be able to add yourself.

children.subject:
Yes, and I can see that after some other Piazza posts many folks have dropped off the list. I've now reduced the WL back to 100 seats.

I'm going to make a separate post but will also respond here: Traditionally the max number of seats for CS 160 has been appx 90 seats. Given attrition estimates of appx 10%, you can figure that the largest this class will expand to is appx 100. which means only another 25 students are likely to be enrolled.

Sometimes I expand a wait list to calm students' angst while things sort themselves out but the fact is that not many more students are likely to get into this class unless there is a radical change made in the way that it's taught and at this point I haven't heard anything of that nature.

What is the likelihood that the class is simulcast into other classrooms like it was in previous semesters? I know logistics for this might be hard, but I'm sure a lot of other students and I would be willing to go to another classroom (not even Jacobs!), since the class is so studio-based.
Thanks! It seems like it closed again though :(
